# Layout Model — Tailwind-docs style (Camp 2)

The layout follows the Tailwind CSS docs pattern: a persistent left Bio sidebar
with content filling the space beside it, inside a capped, centered shell.

## Requirements (verify all after any change)

1. **No "shrunk with space".** Content must never get narrower while empty space
   sits beside it. It fills the space next to the Bio and only narrows when the
   window itself is narrow.
2. **Bio pinned far-left.** The Bio stays at the left edge of the shell — never
   floating inward or centered as a block.
3. **Graceful at every width**, including ultra-wide: the whole shell is capped
   (`size.section.shellWidth`) and centered, so it gets balanced margins instead
   of stretching. Below `size.media.mobile` it stacks into one centered column.

NOTE: We intentionally do NOT require the content to be perfectly viewport-
centered. With a left sidebar that's geometrically impossible without either
shrinking content (breaks #1) or unpinning the Bio (breaks #2). Like Tailwind
docs, content sits beside the Bio, visually balanced by it.

## Structure

```
container (app-shell, full height, centers the shell)
  inner   (grid: `${bioWidth} minmax(0, 1fr)`, max-width: shellWidth)
    Bio   (fixed bioWidth, left)
    main  (content, max-width: bodyWidth, centered in its track)
```

- **>= shellWidth:** shell centers with equal margins; Bio at the left of it.
- **mobile..shellWidth:** shell fills width; Bio left, content fills the rest.
- **< mobile breakpoint:** single centered column, Bio on top.

Do NOT reintroduce: a symmetric 3-col grid that reserves mirror space (causes
"shrunk with space"), or a tightly-capped block that drifts the Bio inward on
normal screens. Tune feel via `bioWidth` / `bodyWidth` / `shellWidth` in `theme.ts`.

## Also preserve

- App-shell scroll: page is locked to viewport height; only `pageArea` scrolls
  (Bio + nav stay fixed). Mobile reverts to normal document scroll.
